00:42:08.100 --> 00:42:11.540
running into issues getting approval to use open source?

00:42:12.739 --> 00:42:15.179
Oh, that's a really good question.

00:42:15.179 --> 00:42:18.500
I think I'll just defer that to Phil.

00:42:18.500 --> 00:42:19.340
I think that's-

00:42:20.979 --> 00:42:22.739
Typically, I mean, I would say for that,

00:42:22.739 --> 00:42:25.060
it usually starts with a champion

00:42:25.060 --> 00:42:28.219
that helps to drive some successes.

00:42:28.219 --> 00:42:30.219
Shiny is great for that because it brings in

00:42:30.219 --> 00:42:32.260
some capabilities into the organization.

00:42:32.260 --> 00:42:34.739
But I mean, most of the big pharma's,

00:42:34.739 --> 00:42:36.379
small and even medium sized ones,

00:42:36.379 --> 00:42:39.540
there's usually a spark that starts with someone.

00:42:39.540 --> 00:42:42.899
And that helps create competency centers

00:42:42.899 --> 00:42:46.139
or data science meetups or hangouts.

00:42:46.139 --> 00:42:48.500
They usually have a way for people to get help.

00:42:48.500 --> 00:42:50.620
And that just starts to snowball into that.

00:42:50.620 --> 00:42:53.100
But R is a great language for starting off

00:42:53.100 --> 00:42:56.780
because you can have a lot of small little successes

00:42:56.780 --> 00:42:58.060
that can really grow.

00:42:58.060 --> 00:43:00.100
And that leads into Python and other languages,

00:43:00.139 --> 00:43:02.620
and JavaScript and Julia and so on.

00:43:02.620 --> 00:43:05.340
So usually it starts with the right person

00:43:05.340 --> 00:43:06.699
at the company driving for it.

00:43:06.699 --> 00:43:08.820
And Rachel has done a lot of good work

00:43:08.820 --> 00:43:11.020
helping those people with the champion page.

00:43:12.820 --> 00:43:16.459
Oh yeah, I will share that in the chat right now too.

00:43:16.459 --> 00:43:19.340
So if anybody is in that position

00:43:19.340 --> 00:43:21.219
