00:43:51.540 --> 00:43:53.580
I'm the director here of life sciences

00:43:53.580 --> 00:43:54.419
and healthcare at RStudio.

00:43:54.419 --> 00:43:57.300
And I work with a lot of the groups in the pharma space.

00:43:57.899 --> 00:44:00.100
Yeah, I remember last year,

00:44:00.100 --> 00:44:02.939
I saw this talk or a version of this talk at R and Pharma.

00:44:02.939 --> 00:44:04.459
And I absolutely was blown away

00:44:04.459 --> 00:44:07.020
because I feel like there's such a big impact right now

00:44:07.020 --> 00:44:08.500
from the data science side.

00:44:08.500 --> 00:44:11.179
And I feel like the common thread among that

00:44:11.179 --> 00:44:13.739
is data wrangling, data management.

00:44:13.739 --> 00:44:16.340
And you're seeing a lot of things coming over

00:44:16.340 --> 00:44:19.300
from data science to helping improve these processes.

00:44:19.300 --> 00:44:20.659
So it's just a great story.

00:44:20.659 --> 00:44:22.739
And I think what you're talking about

00:44:22.739 --> 00:44:25.699
is very applicable across drug discovery,

00:44:25.699 --> 00:44:29.260
research, clinical trials, even post-marketing,

00:44:29.260 --> 00:44:30.979
other divisions of the business.

00:44:30.979 --> 00:44:33.500
I think it's a great example of how data science

00:44:33.500 --> 00:44:35.260
can really help across these areas.

00:44:35.260 --> 00:44:37.139
So fantastic work.

