I see somebody else asked on Slido.

00:44:45.379 --> 00:44:47.780
If you had to guess, what is your team

00:44:47.780 --> 00:44:50.739
or company's mix of R, Python, SAS?

00:44:51.260 --> 00:44:52.100
Hmm.

00:44:52.979 --> 00:44:55.379
This is about BMS.

00:44:55.379 --> 00:44:56.219
That's...

00:44:58.580 --> 00:45:01.500
BMS is a very big organization, as you know,

00:45:01.500 --> 00:45:05.340
and there are a lot of communities within it.

00:45:05.340 --> 00:45:10.340
So my exposure is to the community that I am part of

00:45:12.300 --> 00:45:14.739
in research and early development,

00:45:14.739 --> 00:45:16.500
informatic and predictive sciences.

00:45:16.500 --> 00:45:18.899
And we are heavy users of R,

00:45:18.899 --> 00:45:20.659
at least from the vantage point

00:45:21.580 --> 00:45:24.020
that I have, I would say,

00:45:24.020 --> 00:45:27.500
at least within the location that I am,

00:45:27.500 --> 00:45:32.500
I would say perhaps 70% plus is R.

00:45:34.340 --> 00:45:37.100
And if you go to the clinical side,

00:45:37.100 --> 00:45:39.580
perhaps there's more usage of...

00:45:39.580 --> 00:45:42.219
By clinical, I mean research and early developments,

00:45:42.219 --> 00:45:44.100
more data science flavor.

00:45:44.100 --> 00:45:49.139
Then you have the clinical stats,

00:45:49.139 --> 00:45:51.419
the departments that, historically,

00:45:51.419 --> 00:45:55.139
as in all pharma, there's been more SAS.

00:45:55.139 --> 00:45:58.340
And with some of the flavors of machine learning,

00:45:58.340 --> 00:46:00.739
I think more and more folks are using Python.

00:46:00.739 --> 00:46:02.100
Julia is coming along.

00:46:03.060 --> 00:46:05.219
I can't put a number on it,

00:46:05.219 --> 00:46:08.459
how many folks are using what percentage,

00:46:08.459 --> 00:46:11.540
but that's perhaps the best I can provide.

00:46:12.979 --> 00:46:14.179
Thank you.

00:46:14.179 --> 00:46:15.659
Yeah, sure.

00:46:15.659 --> 00:46:18.419
